<div id="review_1135734618" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1135734618" />
    <a title="Debbi" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/17436935-debbi"><img alt="Debbi" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1633544978p2/17436935.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1135734618?book_show_action=true">Dec 05, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Debbi" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Debbi" href="/user/show/17436935-debbi">Debbi</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1135734618" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4160300798849540803">I braced myself for a very sad book, no parent would wish to outlive their child. Instead, however, the sad event was introduced early and the novel became more of a meditation on sadness. The lives of the characters are quiet but well-considered, I was reminded of Colm Toibin&apos;s or Alice McDermott&apos;s characters. I appreciated the message of faith and the place it held in Ives&apos; story, but I was even more struck by the idea of being able to bravely move forward in the face of tragedy. Wonderful.</span>
  <span id="freeText4160300798849540803" style="display:none">I braced myself for a very sad book, no parent would wish to outlive their child. Instead, however, the sad event was introduced early and the novel became more of a meditation on sadness. The lives of the characters are quiet but well-considered, I was reminded of Colm Toibin's or Alice McDermott's characters. I appreciated the message of faith and the place it held in Ives' story, but I was even more struck by the idea of being able to bravely move forward in the face of tragedy. Wonderful.</span>
  <a data-text-id="4160300798849540803" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


